          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-08-26T22:19:48Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Social Security Disability Fairness Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill allows an individual diagnosed with a terminal illness to receive disability payments under the Old Age, Survivors, and Disability Insurance program during the waiting period for such payments (which typically lasts five months). It also establishes a phased-in payment schedule for such payments. </p> <p>These provisions shall expire January 1, 2025.</p>]]></text>
